Any sample unit taken in accordance with an appropriate sampling plan with an AQL 6.5 (see relevant Codex texts on methods of analysis and sampling) shall be regarded as a "defective" for the respective characteristics as follows:
(a) that exceeds the tolerance for mineral impurities (3.3.2);
(b) that exceeds the tolerance for "free-flowing" (3.3.3);
(c) that exceeds the "Total Allowable Points" for "Visual Defects" in any one or more  of the categories in Table 1 (3.3.6);
(d) that exceeds the tolerance for "Disintegrated" in Table 1 (3.3.6).

